cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper focuses on a new model for local messaging based on network proximity, which falls under the domain of networking. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper describes a mobile mashup that combines Wi-Fi proximity measurements with cloud messaging, which can be seen as a multi-agent system. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses how to combine passive monitoring and notifications, which can be seen as a social network of mobile subscribers. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The cloud-based messaging system described in the paper can be seen as a distributed computing system. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve the use of algorithms and data structures to efficiently monitor and process the proximity measurements.
